26/03/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government plans to send a lawyer and a legal expert to support the defence team of two Macedonians facing trial at The Hague, former Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski and security official Johan Tarculovski. Justice Minister Mihailo Manevski said on Sunday (March 25th) the government has also decided to cover defence costs and pay an allowance to Tarculovski's family. The trial is set to begin on April 16th. Boskovski and Tarculovski are charged with violating the laws or customs of war in connection with a police raid on the village of Ljuboten, in August 2001. 
In other news Sunday, the youth organisations of all the main parties in Macedonia signed a joint declaration. In it, they asked the EU to liberalise the visa regime for Macedonian citizens. (Focus, MIA, Makfax - 25/03/07)
